                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hq3sj8k/manifest/annotation/p1",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>146 Chestnut St</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <date>March 3 1849</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">A gentleman by the name of<lb/>\n                <persName>Berk</persName> said to be a Polish Jew converted to Christianity<lb/> has\n                a plate or picture of <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> &amp; a history of the<lb/>\n                city and professes to be familiar with its history &amp;c.<lb/> I do not expect that\n                you will give me any opinion<lb/> respecting the genuineness of his supposed\n                conversion, but<lb/> I would be obliged if you will tell me whether you know<lb/>\n                any thing to his prejudice apart from this. I have<lb/> been asked to secure his\n                admission to lecture to an assembly<lb/> I should be sorry to introduce him, if his\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">moral char</hi>-<lb/><hi rend=\"underline\">acter</hi> &amp;\n                standing are not irreproachable your reply<lb/> will be confidential.Yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Fred A Packard</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hq3sj8k/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
